This application is repeatedly failing to sync. Common causes:
- Helm template error (bad values, missing key)
- RBAC permission error
- Timeout reaching the target cluster
- Resource conflict or validation error

Actions:
1. argocd app get {{name.name}}
2. argocd app sync {{name.name}} --dry-run
3. Check controller logs: kubectl logs -n argocd -l app.kubernetes.io/name=argocd-application-controller --tail=100 | grep {{name.name}}
4. Check ArgoCD UI for detailed error message
